Madonsela spoke at a seminar at the International Monetary Fund-World Bank meetings in Washington, titled the "Frontiers in Anti-Corruption: Strengthening, Prevention, Tackling Impunity and Changing Perceptions".Â 

She called for citizens to be the eyes and ears against corruption and urged the public to be weary of the corrupt officials who use the poor as their first line of defence.

